The paper deals with shape analysis and matching, which is a common topic in computer graphics and computer vision. The use of functional maps and scalar basis functions suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV), computer graphics (cs.GR), computational geometry (cs.CG), multimedia (cs.MM), or machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on shape analysis and matching, we can eliminate cs.MM and cs.LG as less likely categories. Among the remaining categories, cs.CV and cs.GR are the most likely as they deal with image and shape processing. Finally, cs.CG is also a possible category as it deals with geometric algorithms and data structures.
